REQ-016a full implementation (beyond the initial FIND-007 ordering fix)
==================================================================

The initially-committed FIND-007 fix (capture getChain() before ensureBothWallets()
in the `chain` action) only corrected THAT SINGLE invocation's own displayed value —
it did NOT stop ensureBothWallets() from unconditionally creating
~/.blockrun/.solana-session on every `wallet chain` call, including view-only ones.
Per REQ-016a's literal text ("SHALL create the Solana wallet file ONLY when Solana
is the explicitly-selected or required chain ... SHALL NOT create it as an
unconditional side-effect of view-only ... operations"), that residual gap meant a
fresh user's FIRST `wallet chain` call would still permanently create the file,
flipping ALL FUTURE invocations (of any command) to Solana via REQ-016's rule 3 —
exactly the "permanently rerouting" harm the finding described.

Fixed properly this round:
- src/shell/wallet.ts: added ensureBaseWallet() (Base is always safe to
  create/ensure — REQ-016 rule 4's own default) and peekSolanaWallet() (READ-ONLY —
  checks for an existing ~/.blockrun/.solana-session via the SDK's loadSolanaWallet(),
  never creates one).
- src/commands/wallet.ts's `chain` action: now calls ensureBothWallets() (which
  creates the Solana wallet) ONLY when the caller explicitly requests --chain
  solana. A view-only call (no --chain flag) or an explicit switch to --chain base
  now uses ensureBaseWallet() + peekSolanaWallet() instead — never creating a
  Solana wallet as a side effect. When no Solana wallet exists yet, `solana` is
  reported as `null` (with a human-readable "not yet created" hint), not
  fabricated.

New regression tests:
- test/integration/wallet.test.ts: 3 new mocked tests proving ensureBothWallets()
  is called ONLY on an explicit --chain solana switch, never for view-only calls,
  and that peekSolanaWallet()'s null/existing result is surfaced correctly.
- test/cli/wallet-chain-ordering.test.ts: strengthened to prove, against the REAL
  built binary and a REAL fresh HOME, that REPEATED view-only `wallet chain` calls
  ALL report "base" indefinitely (no cross-invocation flip at all now, not just a
  single-call ordering fix), and that an explicit switch to solana-then-back-to-base
  still correctly persists base via the REQ-016 rule-1 preference file even once a
  real Solana wallet exists on disk.

Full suite: 404/404 pass (was 400 before this round; +4 new tests: 3 mocked
integration + 1 additional real-fs/real-binary case). typecheck clean, build
clean, 3 consecutive full-suite runs all 404/404 (no flakiness, including the
real-network/real-fs wallet tests).
